  "narrative": "Three personal_auto quotes normalized to a 12-month annualized basis. Annualized total cost: Q-A (SafeHarbor Mutual) 1321.00, Q-B (Cardinal Direct) 1272.00, Q-C (Summit Insurance) 1340.00; spread 68.00. Q-B has the lowest annualized total cost, but it omits Uninsured Motorist Bodily Injury, carries higher Collision (1000) and Comprehensive (500) deductibles, and does not list a ride-share-use exclusion that Q-A and Q-C both carry. Q-C carries the highest liability limits (BI 250/500). Differences in coverages, deductibles, limits, exclusions, and endorsements are itemized in the comparison grid; these caveats are why the cost figures are never read in isolation. Comparison of quotes only; not insurance advice, a coverage determination, or a recommendation to purchase. Coverage selection is the customer's decision, made with a licensed producer.",
